description: The product C40 SCC1 covered by this Environmental Product Declaration (EPD) is for specific concrete applications for commercial construction developed and produced by Filomix Ready Mix Concrete for markets in Cairo, Egypt. The design compressive strength is 40 MPa (5,800 psi) at 28 days. Concrete is batched and delivered in accordance with local standards. The producer provides product that meets or exceeds the standards based on standard operating procedures. Warranties and additional information are determined by the producer's terms and conditions. During normal use, hardened concrete is stable and inert and does not pose a significant health or environmental hazard. Fresh, plastic concrete must be managed in accordance with local regulations. concrete is an inert product and can be recycled subject to local regulations.

description: The current assessment has been carried out by General Beton Romania in order to evaluate the environmental impact of its main product, the ready-mix concrete. It is manufactured in plastic state and subsequently delivered on construction sites to create building elements (that could have structural or non-structural functions) or infrastructure elements (i.e. roads, bridges etc.). The ready-mix concrete is manufactured in the Romanian plants owned by General Beton Romania according to the following standards and norms: EN 206:2013+A1:2016 Concrete - Part 1 transposed into Romanian Standard SR EN 206-1: 2014; SR EN 206-1 transposed into Romanian Standard SR 13510:2006/C91:2008; CP NE 012/1-2007; NE 014-2002.
